CONVERSATION GROUP: Hey there. Anything else you'd like to ask me?
I've had a few jobs. Traveled a bit, but shiplife is a bit more work than I care for. Now I serve with the night watch at the docks, and that suits me fine.

This place? You mean Luskan or the Cutlass? Either way, it's pretty much what you'd expect. A bunch of people loosely governed by one rule - mind your own business. Keep that in mind, and you'll be fine.
Perhaps. But since I hardly know ya, I'm not going to vouch for you. And you seem a bit too adventurous to get caught up in that sort of stuff.

Yeah, I do. I was there. Not much to tell, really. There were pretty careful - got in and out before most of us realized anything was up. I'm not sure what all they took, but it couldn't have been much.

The person you'd want to ask is old Bardithas. He actually ran one of them through. I think he picked up some weird item from him, too. I'd introduce you, but he left in a bit of a drunken stupor. But I'm sure he hasn't gone far.
Hands off, begger! Or I'll cut ye'!
Ah, then you're a thief then! Matters not! I'll cut you down all the same!

BK I dropped the "hero bit" because that felt more like a CHA check.
ORIGINAL: I just wanted to hear about the dock raid from the hero of Rethnor.
Hah hah! That I can appreciate! Yep, cowards raided in the dead of the night. Took some things from a smuggling ship we "acquired." Not sure what.
Fought three of 'em myself! Cut one that got away, but plunger my rapier through his friend's gut! Went down like a sack of potatoes.
Nope. A nameless woman. But she did have something on her.
Sure. For a price. A bottle of Arrhenish should do the trick.
Honor? That is the path of a fool. A set of rules meant to restrain us.
Those at the top of the mountain would love for us to abide by their rules.
Our influence is growing rapidly. And more victories will follow.
For I have spoken with an avatar of Graz'zt, and he has told me his plan.
And they will fall, just like the rest of them.
That is quite a task, but those in charge are ripe to fall.
